---
// Funded By Section
---

<div class="py-16">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-4">Funded By</h2>
    <p class="text-center text-base-content/70 mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      This work was funded by Vaulta (formerly EOS) and the Antelope Coalition.
    </p>
    
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <!-- Vaulta Middleware Grant -->
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border-l-4 border-primary">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-primary" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
            Vaulta Middleware Grant
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
            As part of the <a href="https://eosnetwork.com/resources/a-new-era-in-eos-tokenomics-part-i/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="link link-primary">tokenomics</a> approved in mid-2024, Vaulta (formerly EOS) allocated 15M tokens to Middleware initiatives. Greymass received 5M from this allocation to make the blockchain more accessible, reduce onboarding friction, and simplify interactions. This funding enabled development of the EOS Wallet for MetaMask, Web Authenticator (browser-based cloud wallet), Unicove 2.0, and free account creation systems.
          </p>
          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-2">
            <a href="https://eosnetwork.com/resources/eos-metamask-unicove-free-account-creation/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="link link-primary text-sm">
              Read the announcement →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Antelope Coalition Grant -->
      <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg border-l-4 border-secondary">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h3 class="card-title text-lg flex items-center gap-2">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-secondary" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 11H5m14 0a2 2 0 012 2v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2v-6a2 2 0 012-2m14 0V9a2 2 0 00-2-2M5 11V9a2 2 0 012-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h6a2 2 0 012 2v2M7 7h10" />
            </svg>
            Antelope Coalition Grant
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
            In mid-2022, the Antelope Coalition (Vaulta, WAX, Telos, and UX blockchains) funded the development of Wharf, a modular SDK for building blockchain applications across all Antelope-based chains. Born out of the Wallet+ blue paper, this SDK powers wallet integrations, smart contract interactions, and account management with packages including Session Kit, Contract Kit, and Account Kit, and a growing ecosystem of extensions.
          </p>
          <div class="card-actions justify-end mt-2">
            <a href="https://wharfkit.com/blog/the-ports-are-open-v1-0-session-kit-and-new-wharf-website-release" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="link link-secondary text-sm">
              Read about the v1.0 release →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-8">
      <p class="text-sm text-base-content/60">
        These grants enable Greymass to build free and open-source infrastructure that benefits the entire Antelope ecosystem.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
